text: Chiang Kai-hsin (; born 25 December 1990) is a Taiwanese badminton player. In 2007, she reached the girls' doubles semifinal at the World Junior Championships in Waitakere City, New Zealand, winning the bronze medal. In 2009, she won bronze at the East Asian Games in the women's team event. In 2015, she represented National Taiwan Normal University at the World University Badminton Championships in Gwangju, South Korea and won the silver medal in the mixed doubles event.
